<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3883> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3883" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under the Consul Rutilius (App. BC 1.40). His defeat led Rutilius to remove him from command and give his troops to Marius (App. BC 1.41)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3802> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3802" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "3 Since the Legates in the consular armies of 90 B. C. as listed in App. BC 1.40 were ex-Consuls or ex-Praetors, C. Perperna must have held the praetorship by 91. Münzer suggests 92, the consulship of M. Perperna." .
